main event: Two jet aircrafts were tracked by radar and observed by two operators at approximately 35,000 ft., moving rapidly in a weaving fashion before disappearing from the radar.
interesting points: The objects were tracked for approximately 25 minutes by radar operators., The targets appeared as two bright returns moving at approximately 600 knots., 1/Lt. Sandoval and 1/Lt. Smith observed the objects at a high angle of elevation., The sighting occurred near Montan AFB, Arizona, which is close to the sun's position., The objects were noted to be of metallic nature and traveling in an erratic course.
sighted object: two metallic objects in the sky
witness description: 1/Lt. Sandoval and 1/Lt. Smith, both pilots in the U.S. Air Force
